{"artefact":[["_response_info",{"status":"ok"}],["title","Special educational needs and disability tribunal"],["id","https://contentapi.production.alphagov.co.uk/special-educational-needs-disability-tribunal.json"],["web_url","https://www.gov.uk/special-educational-needs-disability-tribunal"],["format","guide"],["details",{"need_id":"2396","business_proposition":false,"alternative_title":"I","overview":"How to appeal to the special educational needs tribunal to get extra help to support your child in school","video_summary":"","video_url":"","updated_at":"2012-10-02T12:14:18+00:00","parts":[{"web_url":"https://www.gov.uk/special-educational-needs-disability-tribunal/overview","slug":"overview","order":1,"title":"Overview","body":"<p>You can appeal to the special educational needs and disability tribunal if you disagree with the council&rsquo;s decisions about your child&rsquo;s special educational needs.</p>\n\n<p>For example, the council may not agree that your child needs extra support in the classroom to help them with learning difficulties.</p>\n\n<p>You can also appeal to the tribunal if the school or council has discriminated against your disabled child.</p>\n\n<h2>Special educational needs appeals</h2>\n\n<p>You can appeal for a number of reasons, eg if the council refuses to:</p>\n\n<ul>\n  <li>assess your child&rsquo;s special educational needs</li>\n  <li>make a statement of their needs</li>\n  <li>reassess their needs</li>\n</ul>\n\n<div class=\"application-notice help-notice\">\n<p>You usually have to appeal to the tribunal within 2 months of getting the council\u2019s decision letter.</p>\n</div>\n\n<h2>Help and advice</h2>\n\n<p>You may want to get <a rel=\"external\" href=\"http://legaladviserfinder.justice.gov.uk/AdviserSearch.do\" title=\"legal advice\">legal advice</a> before you appeal.</p>\n\n<p>You could be entitled to <a href=\"/legal-aid\" title=\"legal aid\">legal aid</a> to pay for a meeting with a solicitor.</p>\n\n<p>You can also get help and advice from your local Parent Partnership Service. </p>\n\n<p>Contact the <a rel=\"external\" href=\"http://www.parentpartnership.org.uk\" title=\"National Parent Partnership Network\">National Parent Partnership Network</a> for details of your nearest service.</p>\n\n<div class=\"contact\">\n<p><strong>National Parent Partnership Network</strong>  <br />\n<strong>Email:</strong> <a href=\"&#109;&#097;&#105;&#108;&#116;&#111;:&#110;&#112;&#112;&#110;&#064;&#110;&#099;&#098;&#046;&#111;&#114;&#103;&#046;&#117;&#107;\">&#110;&#112;&#112;&#110;&#064;&#110;&#099;&#098;&#046;&#111;&#114;&#103;&#046;&#117;&#107;</a><br />\n<strong>Telephone:</strong> 020 7843 6958</p>\n</div>\n\n<h2>You live in Wales</h2>\n\n<p>If you live in Wales, you can appeal to the <a rel=\"external\" href=\"http://www.sentw.gov.uk/\" title=\"Special Educational Needs Tribunal for Wales\">Special Educational Needs Tribunal for Wales.</a></p>\n"},{"web_url":"https://www.gov.uk/special-educational-needs-disability-tribunal/before-you-appeal","slug":"before-you-appeal","order":2,"title":"Before you appeal","body":"<p>Before you appeal, see if you can discuss the problem with your school or the council.</p>\n\n<p>A free mediation service in your area can help you do this.</p>\n\n<p>The service will bring you, the school and the council together to see if you can work out a solution.</p>\n\n<p>You don&rsquo;t have to try this, but if you do it won&rsquo;t affect your right to appeal.</p>\n\n<h2>Special educational needs mediation services</h2>\n\n<h3>East Midlands</h3>\n\n<div class=\"contact\">\n<p><a href=\"http://www.togethertrust.org.uk/\" title=\"Together Trust\" rel=\"external\">Together Trust</a><br />\n<strong>Email:</strong> <a href=\"&#109;&#097;&#105;&#108;&#116;&#111;:&#100;&#114;&#115;&#064;&#116;&#111;&#103;&#101;&#116;&#104;&#101;&#114;&#116;&#114;&#117;&#115;&#116;&#046;&#111;&#114;&#103;&#046;&#117;&#107;\">&#100;&#114;&#115;&#064;&#116;&#111;&#103;&#101;&#116;&#104;&#101;&#114;&#116;&#114;&#117;&#115;&#116;&#046;&#111;&#114;&#103;&#046;&#117;&#107;</a><br />\n<strong>Telephone:</strong> 0161 283 4801<br />\n<strong>Fax:</strong> 0161 283 4848</p>\n</div>\n\n<h3>East of England</h3>\n\n<h4>Essex</h4>\n\n<div class=\"contact\">\n<p><a href=\"http://www.timeforpeople.co.uk/\" title=\"Independent SEN Mediation Service\" rel=\"external\">Independent SEN Mediation Service</a><br />\n<strong>Email:</strong> <a href=\"&#109;&#097;&#105;&#108;&#116;&#111;:&#102;&#114;&#097;&#110;&#099;&#101;&#115;&#098;&#101;&#101;&#064;&#116;&#105;&#109;&#101;&#102;&#111;&#114;&#112;&#101;&#111;&#112;&#108;&#101;&#046;&#099;&#111;&#046;&#117;&#107;\">&#102;&#114;&#097;&#110;&#099;&#101;&#115;&#098;&#101;&#101;&#064;&#116;&#105;&#109;&#101;&#102;&#111;&#114;&#112;&#101;&#111;&#112;&#108;&#101;&#046;&#099;&#111;&#046;&#117;&#107;</a> <br />\nor <a href=\"&#109;&#097;&#105;&#108;&#116;&#111;:&#115;&#109;&#099;&#114;&#046;&#109;&#101;&#100;&#105;&#097;&#116;&#105;&#111;&#110;&#064;&#098;&#116;&#105;&#110;&#116;&#101;&#114;&#110;&#101;&#116;&#046;&#099;&#111;&#109;\">&#115;&#109;&#099;&#114;&#046;&#109;&#101;&#100;&#105;&#097;&#116;&#105;&#111;&#110;&#064;&#098;&#116;&#105;&#110;&#116;&#101;&#114;&#110;&#101;&#116;&#046;&#099;&#111;&#109;</a><br />\n<strong>Telephone:</strong> 01284 828 285<br />\nor 01493 701 383</p>\n</div>\n\n<h4>Norfolk</h4>\n\n<div class=\"contact\">\n<p><a href=\"http://www.mediation-works.co.uk/\" title=\"Mediation Works\" rel=\"external\">Mediation Works</a><br />\n<strong>Email:</strong> <a href=\"&#109;&#097;&#105;&#108;&#116;&#111;:&#115;&#101;&#110;&#064;&#109;&#101;&#100;&#105;&#097;&#116;&#105;&#111;&#110;&#045;&#119;&#111;&#114;&#107;&#115;&#046;&#099;&#111;&#046;&#117;&#107;\">&#115;&#101;&#110;&#064;&#109;&#101;&#100;&#105;&#097;&#116;&#105;&#111;&#110;&#045;&#119;&#111;&#114;&#107;&#115;&#046;&#099;&#111;&#046;&#117;&#107;</a><br />\n<strong>Telephone:</strong> 01952 275 038<br />\n<strong>Fax:</strong> 01952 224 289</p>\n</div>\n\n<h4>Suffolk</h4>\n\n<div class=\"contact\">\n<p>Cambridge Family Mediation Service<br />\n<strong>Email:</strong> <a href=\"&#109;&#097;&#105;&#108;&#116;&#111;:&#102;&#097;&#109;&#105;&#108;&#105;&#101;&#115;&#064;&#099;&#097;&#109;&#098;&#114;&#105;&#100;&#103;&#101;&#102;&#109;&#115;&#046;&#099;&#111;&#046;&#117;&#107;\">&#102;&#097;&#109;&#105;&#108;&#105;&#101;&#115;&#064;&#099;&#097;&#109;&#098;&#114;&#105;&#100;&#103;&#101;&#102;&#109;&#115;&#046;&#099;&#111;&#046;&#117;&#107;</a><br />\n<strong>Telephone:</strong> 01223 576 308</p>\n</div>\n\n<h3>Greater London</h3>\n\n<div class=\"contact\">\n<p><a href=\"http://www.kids.org.uk/\" title=\"KIDS\" rel=\"external\">KIDS</a><br />\n<strong>Email:</strong> <a href=\"&#109;&#097;&#105;&#108;&#116;&#111;:&#065;&#117;&#100;&#114;&#101;&#121;&#046;&#100;&#111;&#114;&#105;&#118;&#097;&#108;&#064;&#107;&#105;&#100;&#115;&#046;&#111;&#114;&#103;&#046;&#117;&#107;\">&#065;&#117;&#100;&#114;&#101;&#121;&#046;&#100;&#111;&#114;&#105;&#118;&#097;&#108;&#064;&#107;&#105;&#100;&#115;&#046;&#111;&#114;&#103;&#046;&#117;&#107;</a><br />\n<strong>Telephone:</strong> 020 7837 2900<br />\n<strong>Fax:</strong> 020 7520 0406</p>\n</div>\n\n<h3>North East England</h3>\n\n<div class=\"contact\">\n<p><a href=\"http://www.mediation-works.co.uk/\" title=\"Mediation Works\" rel=\"external\">Mediation Works</a><br />\n<strong>Email:</strong> <a href=\"&#109;&#097;&#105;&#108;&#116;&#111;:&#111;&#102;&#102;&#105;&#099;&#101;&#064;&#109;&#105;&#100;&#108;&#097;&#110;&#100;&#115;&#115;&#101;&#110;&#109;&#101;&#100;&#105;&#097;&#116;&#105;&#111;&#110;&#046;&#099;&#111;&#109;\">&#111;&#102;&#102;&#105;&#099;&#101;&#064;&#109;&#105;&#100;&#108;&#097;&#110;&#100;&#115;&#115;&#101;&#110;&#109;&#101;&#100;&#105;&#097;&#116;&#105;&#111;&#110;&#046;&#099;&#111;&#109;</a><br />\n<strong>Telephone:</strong> 01952 275 038<br />\n<strong>Fax:</strong> 01952 224 281</p>\n</div>\n\n<h3>North West England</h3>\n\n<div class=\"contact\">\n<p>Mediation and Disagreement Resolution Service<br />\n<strong>Email:</strong> <a href=\"&#109;&#097;&#105;&#108;&#116;&#111;:&#109;&#100;&#114;&#115;&#064;&#108;&#097;&#110;&#099;&#097;&#115;&#104;&#105;&#114;&#101;&#046;&#103;&#111;&#118;&#046;&#117;&#107;\">&#109;&#100;&#114;&#115;&#064;&#108;&#097;&#110;&#099;&#097;&#115;&#104;&#105;&#114;&#101;&#046;&#103;&#111;&#118;&#046;&#117;&#107;</a><br />\n<strong>Telephone/Fax:</strong> 01772 537 927</p>\n</div>\n\n<h3>South East England</h3>\n\n<div class=\"contact\">\n<p><a href=\"http://www.globalmediation.co.uk/\" title=\"Global Mediation\" rel=\"external\">Global Mediation</a><br />\n<strong>Email:</strong> <a href=\"&#109;&#097;&#105;&#108;&#116;&#111;:&#105;&#110;&#102;&#111;&#064;&#103;&#108;&#111;&#098;&#097;&#108;&#109;&#101;&#100;&#105;&#097;&#116;&#105;&#111;&#110;&#046;&#099;&#111;&#046;&#117;&#107;\">&#105;&#110;&#102;&#111;&#064;&#103;&#108;&#111;&#098;&#097;&#108;&#109;&#101;&#100;&#105;&#097;&#116;&#105;&#111;&#110;&#046;&#099;&#111;&#046;&#117;&#107;</a><br />\n<strong>Telephone:</strong> 0800 064 4488<br />\n<strong>Fax:</strong> 0208 441 4101</p>\n</div>\n\n<h3>South West England</h3>\n\n<div class=\"contact\">\n<p><a href=\"http://www.wessexmediation.co.uk/\" title=\"Wessex Mediation Service\" rel=\"external\">Wessex Mediation Service</a><br />\n<strong>Email:</strong> <a href=\"&#109;&#097;&#105;&#108;&#116;&#111;:&#105;&#110;&#102;&#111;&#064;&#119;&#101;&#115;&#115;&#101;&#120;&#109;&#101;&#100;&#105;&#097;&#116;&#105;&#111;&#110;&#046;&#099;&#111;&#046;&#117;&#107;\">&#105;&#110;&#102;&#111;&#064;&#119;&#101;&#115;&#115;&#101;&#120;&#109;&#101;&#100;&#105;&#097;&#116;&#105;&#111;&#110;&#046;&#099;&#111;&#046;&#117;&#107;</a><br />\n<strong>Telephone:</strong> 08450 529 487<br />\n<strong>Fax:</strong> 01823 352 210</p>\n</div>\n\n<h3>West Midlands</h3>\n\n<div class=\"contact\">\n<p><a href=\"http://www.mediation-works.co.uk/\" title=\"Mediation Works\" rel=\"external\">Mediation Works</a><br />\n<strong>Email:</strong> <a href=\"&#109;&#097;&#105;&#108;&#116;&#111;:&#111;&#102;&#102;&#105;&#099;&#101;&#064;&#109;&#105;&#100;&#108;&#097;&#110;&#100;&#115;&#115;&#101;&#110;&#109;&#101;&#100;&#105;&#097;&#116;&#105;&#111;&#110;&#046;&#099;&#111;&#109;\">&#111;&#102;&#102;&#105;&#099;&#101;&#064;&#109;&#105;&#100;&#108;&#097;&#110;&#100;&#115;&#115;&#101;&#110;&#109;&#101;&#100;&#105;&#097;&#116;&#105;&#111;&#110;&#046;&#099;&#111;&#109;</a><br />\n<strong>Telephone:</strong> 01952 275 038<br />\n<strong>Fax:</strong> 01952 224 281</p>\n</div>\n"},{"web_url":"https://www.gov.uk/special-educational-needs-disability-tribunal/appeal-to-tribunal","slug":"appeal-to-tribunal","order":3,"title":"Appeal to the tribunal","body":"<p>To appeal, fill in the form below, giving reasons why you disagree with the council&rsquo;s decision.</p>\n\n<div class=\"form-download\">\n<p><a href=\"http://www.justice.gov.uk/downloads/forms/tribunals/send/sen-appeal-form.pdf\" title=\"Download 'Appeal form' (PDF, 44KB)\" rel=\"external\">Download \u2018Appeal form\u2019 (PDF, 44KB)</a></p>\n</div>\n\n<p>Send this, with the documents listed on the form, to:</p>\n\n<div class=\"address\"><div class=\"adr org fn\"><p>\n First-tier Tribunal (Special Educational Needs and Disability)  \nMowden Hall  \n<br />Staindrop Road  \n<br />Darlington  \n<br />DL3 9BG \n</p></div></div>\n\n<div class=\"contact\">\n<p><strong>Email:</strong> <a href=\"&#109;&#097;&#105;&#108;&#116;&#111;:&#115;&#101;&#110;&#100;&#105;&#115;&#116;&#113;&#117;&#101;&#114;&#105;&#101;&#115;&#064;&#104;&#109;&#099;&#116;&#115;&#046;&#103;&#115;&#105;&#046;&#103;&#111;&#118;&#046;&#117;&#107;\">&#115;&#101;&#110;&#100;&#105;&#115;&#116;&#113;&#117;&#101;&#114;&#105;&#101;&#115;&#064;&#104;&#109;&#099;&#116;&#115;&#046;&#103;&#115;&#105;&#046;&#103;&#111;&#118;&#046;&#117;&#107;</a><br />\n<strong>Telephone:</strong> 01325 392 760<br />\n<strong>Fax:</strong> 01325 391 080<br />\nor 01325 391 310</p>\n</div>\n\n<p>It usually takes 5 months to get a decision on a case from the date of the appeal.</p>\n"},{"web_url":"https://www.gov.uk/special-educational-needs-disability-tribunal/going-to-tribunal-hearing","slug":"going-to-tribunal-hearing","order":4,"title":"Going to a tribunal hearing","body":"<p>The tribunal will hold the hearing at a regional hearing centre.</p>\n\n<p>You don&rsquo;t have to go to the hearing, but you may want to ask the council questions and put your case in person.</p>\n\n<p>Fill in the attendance form if you want to bring:</p>\n\n<ul>\n  <li>someone to represent you</li>\n  <li>someone to support you at the hearing</li>\n</ul>\n\n<div class=\"form-download\">\n<p><a href=\"http://www.justice.gov.uk/downloads/forms/tribunals/send/parents-attend-form.pdf\" title=\"Download 'attendance form' (PDF, 61KB)\" rel=\"external\">Download \u2018attendance form\u2019 (PDF, 61KB)</a></p>\n</div>\n\n<h2>Who will be at the hearing</h2>\n\n<p>The hearing will usually be attended by:</p>\n\n<ul>\n  <li>up to 3 tribunal members</li>\n  <li>a tribunal clerk</li>\n  <li>someone representing the council</li>\n  <li>any witnesses</li>\n</ul>\n\n<p>Both parents can attend.</p>\n\n<p>You are usually allowed to bring up to 3 witnesses to a hearing. </p>\n\n<p>You may not have to call professional witnesses if they have already written a report on your child.</p>\n\n<p>You can bring your child, but you&rsquo;ll have to arrange for someone to look after them when they&rsquo;re not in the hearing room.</p>\n\n<h2>Travel costs</h2>\n\n<p>You and your witnesses will be able to claim for travel expenses for going to the hearing.</p>\n\n<p>If you bring a friend or relative to the hearing, you will also be able to claim for their travel costs.</p>\n\n<p>The tribunal clerk will give you the forms you need.</p>\n\n<div class=\"application-notice info-notice\">\n<p>You will usually get the tribunal\u2019s decision in the post within 10 days of the hearing.</p>\n</div>\n"},{"web_url":"https://www.gov.uk/special-educational-needs-disability-tribunal/if-you-win-your-appeal","slug":"if-you-win-your-appeal","order":5,"title":"If you win your appeal","body":"<p>If you win your appeal, the council must act on the tribunal&rsquo;s decision within a fixed amount of time:</p>\n\n<table>\n  <thead>\n    <tr>\n      <th>Decision</th>\n      <th>When council must act on decision</th>\n    </tr>\n  </thead>\n  <tbody>\n    <tr>\n      <td>Start assessment or reassessment</td>\n      <td>within 4 weeks</td>\n    </tr>\n    <tr>\n      <td>Make statement of child&rsquo;s needs</td>\n      <td>within 5 weeks</td>\n    </tr>\n    <tr>\n      <td>Change statement</td>\n      <td>within 5 weeks</td>\n    </tr>\n    <tr>\n      <td>Change the school</td>\n      <td>within 2 weeks</td>\n    </tr>\n    <tr>\n      <td>Continue with statement of child&rsquo;s needs</td>\n      <td>at once</td>\n    </tr>\n    <tr>\n      <td>Cancel a statement</td>\n      <td>at once</td>\n    </tr>\n  </tbody>\n</table>\n\n<p>If the council doesn&rsquo;t keep to the decision you can complain to the Local Government Ombudsman:</p>\n\n<div class=\"contact\">\n<p><strong>Local Government Ombudsman</strong><br />\n<a href=\"http://www.lgo.org.uk/forms/ShowForm.asp?fm_fid=74\" title=\"enquiry form\" rel=\"external\">Enquiry form</a><br />\n<strong>Telephone:</strong> 0300 061 0614</p>\n</div>\n\n<div class=\"address\"><div class=\"adr org fn\"><p>\n Local Government Ombudsman    \n\n<br />PO Box 4771  \n<br />Coventry  \n<br />CV4 0EH \n</p></div></div>\n"},{"web_url":"https://www.gov.uk/special-educational-needs-disability-tribunal/if-you-lose-your-appeal","slug":"if-you-lose-your-appeal","order":6,"title":"If you lose your appeal","body":"<p>If you lose your case, you may be able to:</p>\n\n<ul>\n  <li>ask the tribunal to look at the case again, or overturn it</li>\n  <li>appeal against the decision</li>\n</ul>\n\n<p>The tribunal will send you details of how you can ask for the decision to be reviewed or &lsquo;set aside&rsquo;.</p>\n\n<p>To appeal against the decision, fill in the <a rel=\"external\" href=\"http://hmctsformfinder.justice.gov.uk/HMCTS/GetForm.do?court_forms_id=2767\" title=\"application for permission to appeal form\">application for permission to appeal form.</a></p>\n\n<p>Send this to the special educational needs tribunal:</p>\n\n<div class=\"address\"><div class=\"adr org fn\"><p>\n First-tier Tribunal (Special Educational Needs and Disability)  \nMowden Hall  \n<br />Staindrop Road  \n<br />Darlington  \n<br />DL3 9BG \n</p></div></div>\n\n<div class=\"contact\">\n<p><strong>Email:</strong> <a href=\"&#109;&#097;&#105;&#108;&#116;&#111;:&#115;&#101;&#110;&#100;&#105;&#115;&#116;&#113;&#117;&#101;&#114;&#105;&#101;&#115;&#064;&#104;&#109;&#099;&#116;&#115;&#046;&#103;&#115;&#105;&#046;&#103;&#111;&#118;&#046;&#117;&#107;\">&#115;&#101;&#110;&#100;&#105;&#115;&#116;&#113;&#117;&#101;&#114;&#105;&#101;&#115;&#064;&#104;&#109;&#099;&#116;&#115;&#046;&#103;&#115;&#105;&#046;&#103;&#111;&#118;&#046;&#117;&#107;</a><br />\n<strong>Telephone:</strong> 01325 392 760<br />\n<strong>Fax:</strong> 01325 391 080<br />\nor 01325 391 310</p>\n</div>\n\n<div class=\"application-notice help-notice\">\n<p>You must appeal within 28 days of the date of the tribunal\u2019s decision letter.</p>\n</div>\n\n<p>If you&rsquo;re given permission to appeal, the case will be heard by a higher tribunal called the <a rel=\"external\" href=\"http://www.justice.gov.uk/tribunals/aa\" title=\"Upper Tribunal (Administrative Appeals Chamber)\">Upper Tribunal (Administrative Appeals Chamber).</a></p>\n"}]}],["tags",[{"title":"Courts, sentencing and tribunals","id":"https://contentapi.production.alphagov.co.uk/tags/justice%2Fcourts-sentencing-tribunals.json","web_url":null,"details":{"description":"Attending courts, paying fines, appealing a sentence and tribunals","type":"section"},"content_with_tag":{"id":"https://contentapi.production.alphagov.co.uk/with_tag.json?tag=justice%2Fcourts-sentencing-tribunals","web_url":"https://www.gov.uk/browse/justice/courts-sentencing-tribunals"},"parent":{"title":"Crime, justice and the law","id":"https://contentapi.production.alphagov.co.uk/tags/justice.json","web_url":null,"details":{"description":"Legal processes, courts and the police","type":"section"},"content_with_tag":{"id":"https://contentapi.production.alphagov.co.uk/with_tag.json?tag=justice","web_url":"https://www.gov.uk/browse/justice"},"parent":null}},{"title":"Reporting crimes and getting compensation","id":"https://contentapi.production.alphagov.co.uk/tags/justice%2Freporting-crimes-compensation.json","web_url":null,"details":{"description":"Including criminal injuries compensation and reporting suspected crimes","type":"section"},"content_with_tag":{"id":"https://contentapi.production.alphagov.co.uk/with_tag.json?tag=justice%2Freporting-crimes-compensation","web_url":"https://www.gov.uk/browse/justice/reporting-crimes-compensation"},"parent":{"title":"Crime, justice and the law","id":"https://contentapi.production.alphagov.co.uk/tags/justice.json","web_url":null,"details":{"description":"Legal processes, courts and the police","type":"section"},"content_with_tag":{"id":"https://contentapi.production.alphagov.co.uk/with_tag.json?tag=justice","web_url":"https://www.gov.uk/browse/justice"},"parent":null}}]],["related",[{"title":"Children with special educational needs","id":"https://contentapi.production.alphagov.co.uk/children-with-special-educational-needs.json","web_url":"https://www.gov.uk/children-with-special-educational-needs","format":"guide","details":{"need_id":"1345","business_proposition":false}}]]],"parts":[{"part":{"web_url":"https://www.gov.uk/special-educational-needs-disability-tribunal/overview","slug":"overview","order":1,"title":"Overview","body":"<p>You can appeal to the special educational needs and disability tribunal if you disagree with the council&rsquo;s decisions about your child&rsquo;s special educational needs.</p>\n\n<p>For example, the council may not agree that your child needs extra support in the classroom to help them with learning difficulties.</p>\n\n<p>You can also appeal to the tribunal if the school or council has discriminated against your disabled child.</p>\n\n<h2>Special educational needs appeals</h2>\n\n<p>You can appeal for a number of reasons, eg if the council refuses to:</p>\n\n<ul>\n  <li>assess your child&rsquo;s special educational needs</li>\n  <li>make a statement of their needs</li>\n  <li>reassess their needs</li>\n</ul>\n\n<div class=\"application-notice help-notice\">\n<p>You usually have to appeal to the tribunal within 2 months of getting the council\u2019s decision letter.</p>\n</div>\n\n<h2>Help and advice</h2>\n\n<p>You may want to get <a rel=\"external\" href=\"http://legaladviserfinder.justice.gov.uk/AdviserSearch.do\" title=\"legal advice\">legal advice</a> before you appeal.</p>\n\n<p>You could be entitled to <a href=\"/legal-aid\" title=\"legal aid\">legal aid</a> to pay for a meeting with a solicitor.</p>\n\n<p>You can also get help and advice from your local Parent Partnership Service. </p>\n\n<p>Contact the <a rel=\"external\" href=\"http://www.parentpartnership.org.uk\" title=\"National Parent Partnership Network\">National Parent Partnership Network</a> for details of your nearest service.</p>\n\n<div class=\"contact\">\n<p><strong>National Parent Partnership Network</strong>  <br />\n<strong>Email:</strong> <a href=\"&#109;&#097;&#105;&#108;&#116;&#111;:&#110;&#112;&#112;&#110;&#064;&#110;&#099;&#098;&#046;&#111;&#114;&#103;&#046;&#117;&#107;\">&#110;&#112;&#112;&#110;&#064;&#110;&#099;&#098;&#046;&#111;&#114;&#103;&#046;&#117;&#107;</a><br />\n<strong>Telephone:</strong> 020 7843 6958</p>\n</div>\n\n<h2>You live in Wales</h2>\n\n<p>If you live in Wales, you can appeal to the <a rel=\"external\" href=\"http://www.sentw.gov.uk/\" title=\"Special Educational Needs Tribunal for Wales\">Special Educational Needs Tribunal for Wales.</a></p>\n"}},{"part":{"web_url":"https://www.gov.uk/special-educational-needs-disability-tribunal/before-you-appeal","slug":"before-you-appeal","order":2,"title":"Before you appeal","body":"<p>Before you appeal, see if you can discuss the problem with your school or the council.</p>\n\n<p>A free mediation service in your area can help you do this.</p>\n\n<p>The service will bring you, the school and the council together to see if you can work out a solution.</p>\n\n<p>You don&rsquo;t have to try this, but if you do it won&rsquo;t affect your right to appeal.</p>\n\n<h2>Special educational needs mediation services</h2>\n\n<h3>East Midlands</h3>\n\n<div class=\"contact\">\n<p><a href=\"http://www.togethertrust.org.uk/\" title=\"Together Trust\" rel=\"external\">Together Trust</a><br />\n<strong>Email:</strong> <a href=\"&#109;&#097;&#105;&#108;&#116;&#111;:&#100;&#114;&#115;&#064;&#116;&#111;&#103;&#101;&#116;&#104;&#101;&#114;&#116;&#114;&#117;&#115;&#116;&#046;&#111;&#114;&#103;&#046;&#117;&#107;\">&#100;&#114;&#115;&#064;&#116;&#111;&#103;&#101;&#116;&#104;&#101;&#114;&#116;&#114;&#117;&#115;&#116;&#046;&#111;&#114;&#103;&#046;&#117;&#107;</a><br />\n<strong>Telephone:</strong> 0161 283 4801<br />\n<strong>Fax:</strong> 0161 283 4848</p>\n</div>\n\n<h3>East of England</h3>\n\n<h4>Essex</h4>\n\n<div class=\"contact\">\n<p><a href=\"http://www.timeforpeople.co.uk/\" title=\"Independent SEN Mediation Service\" rel=\"external\">Independent SEN Mediation Service</a><br />\n<strong>Email:</strong> <a href=\"&#109;&#097;&#105;&#108;&#116;&#111;:&#102;&#114;&#097;&#110;&#099;&#101;&#115;&#098;&#101;&#101;&#064;&#116;&#105;&#109;&#101;&#102;&#111;&#114;&#112;&#101;&#111;&#112;&#108;&#101;&#046;&#099;&#111;&#046;&#117;&#107;\">&#102;&#114;&#097;&#110;&#099;&#101;&#115;&#098;&#101;&#101;&#064;&#116;&#105;&#109;&#101;&#102;&#111;&#114;&#112;&#101;&#111;&#112;&#108;&#101;&#046;&#099;&#111;&#046;&#117;&#107;</a> <br />\nor <a href=\"&#109;&#097;&#105;&#108;&#116;&#111;:&#115;&#109;&#099;&#114;&#046;&#109;&#101;&#100;&#105;&#097;&#116;&#105;&#111;&#110;&#064;&#098;&#116;&#105;&#110;&#116;&#101;&#114;&#110;&#101;&#116;&#046;&#099;&#111;&#109;\">&#115;&#109;&#099;&#114;&#046;&#109;&#101;&#100;&#105;&#097;&#116;&#105;&#111;&#110;&#064;&#098;&#116;&#105;&#110;&#116;&#101;&#114;&#110;&#101;&#116;&#046;&#099;&#111;&#109;</a><br />\n<strong>Telephone:</strong> 01284 828 285<br />\nor 01493 701 383</p>\n</div>\n\n<h4>Norfolk</h4>\n\n<div class=\"contact\">\n<p><a href=\"http://www.mediation-works.co.uk/\" title=\"Mediation Works\" rel=\"external\">Mediation Works</a><br />\n<strong>Email:</strong> <a href=\"&#109;&#097;&#105;&#108;&#116;&#111;:&#115;&#101;&#110;&#064;&#109;&#101;&#100;&#105;&#097;&#116;&#105;&#111;&#110;&#045;&#119;&#111;&#114;&#107;&#115;&#046;&#099;&#111;&#046;&#117;&#107;\">&#115;&#101;&#110;&#064;&#109;&#101;&#100;&#105;&#097;&#116;&#105;&#111;&#110;&#045;&#119;&#111;&#114;&#107;&#115;&#046;&#099;&#111;&#046;&#117;&#107;</a><br />\n<strong>Telephone:</strong> 01952 275 038<br />\n<strong>Fax:</strong> 01952 224 289</p>\n</div>\n\n<h4>Suffolk</h4>\n\n<div class=\"contact\">\n<p>Cambridge Family Mediation Service<br />\n<strong>Email:</strong> <a href=\"&#109;&#097;&#105;&#108;&#116;&#111;:&#102;&#097;&#109;&#105;&#108;&#105;&#101;&#115;&#064;&#099;&#097;&#109;&#098;&#114;&#105;&#100;&#103;&#101;&#102;&#109;&#115;&#046;&#099;&#111;&#046;&#117;&#107;\">&#102;&#097;&#109;&#105;&#108;&#105;&#101;&#115;&#064;&#099;&#097;&#109;&#098;&#114;&#105;&#100;&#103;&#101;&#102;&#109;&#115;&#046;&#099;&#111;&#046;&#117;&#107;</a><br />\n<strong>Telephone:</strong> 01223 576 308</p>\n</div>\n\n<h3>Greater London</h3>\n\n<div class=\"contact\">\n<p><a href=\"http://www.kids.org.uk/\" title=\"KIDS\" rel=\"external\">KIDS</a><br />\n<strong>Email:</strong> <a href=\"&#109;&#097;&#105;&#108;&#116;&#111;:&#065;&#117;&#100;&#114;&#101;&#121;&#046;&#100;&#111;&#114;&#105;&#118;&#097;&#108;&#064;&#107;&#105;&#100;&#115;&#046;&#111;&#114;&#103;&#046;&#117;&#107;\">&#065;&#117;&#100;&#114;&#101;&#121;&#046;&#100;&#111;&#114;&#105;&#118;&#097;&#108;&#064;&#107;&#105;&#100;&#115;&#046;&#111;&#114;&#103;&#046;&#117;&#107;</a><br />\n<strong>Telephone:</strong> 020 7837 2900<br />\n<strong>Fax:</strong> 020 7520 0406</p>\n</div>\n\n<h3>North East England</h3>\n\n<div class=\"contact\">\n<p><a href=\"http://www.mediation-works.co.uk/\" title=\"Mediation Works\" rel=\"external\">Mediation Works</a><br />\n<strong>Email:</strong> <a href=\"&#109;&#097;&#105;&#108;&#116;&#111;:&#111;&#102;&#102;&#105;&#099;&#101;&#064;&#109;&#105;&#100;&#108;&#097;&#110;&#100;&#115;&#115;&#101;&#110;&#109;&#101;&#100;&#105;&#097;&#116;&#105;&#111;&#110;&#046;&#099;&#111;&#109;\">&#111;&#102;&#102;&#105;&#099;&#101;&#064;&#109;&#105;&#100;&#108;&#097;&#110;&#100;&#115;&#115;&#101;&#110;&#109;&#101;&#100;&#105;&#097;&#116;&#105;&#111;&#110;&#046;&#099;&#111;&#109;</a><br />\n<strong>Telephone:</strong> 01952 275 038<br />\n<strong>Fax:</strong> 01952 224 281</p>\n</div>\n\n<h3>North West England</h3>\n\n<div class=\"contact\">\n<p>Mediation and Disagreement Resolution Service<br />\n<strong>Email:</strong> <a href=\"&#109;&#097;&#105;&#108;&#116;&#111;:&#109;&#100;&#114;&#115;&#064;&#108;&#097;&#110;&#099;&#097;&#115;&#104;&#105;&#114;&#101;&#046;&#103;&#111;&#118;&#046;&#117;&#107;\">&#109;&#100;&#114;&#115;&#064;&#108;&#097;&#110;&#099;&#097;&#115;&#104;&#105;&#114;&#101;&#046;&#103;&#111;&#118;&#046;&#117;&#107;</a><br />\n<strong>Telephone/Fax:</strong> 01772 537 927</p>\n</div>\n\n<h3>South East England</h3>\n\n<div class=\"contact\">\n<p><a href=\"http://www.globalmediation.co.uk/\" title=\"Global Mediation\" rel=\"external\">Global Mediation</a><br />\n<strong>Email:</strong> <a href=\"&#109;&#097;&#105;&#108;&#116;&#111;:&#105;&#110;&#102;&#111;&#064;&#103;&#108;&#111;&#098;&#097;&#108;&#109;&#101;&#100;&#105;&#097;&#116;&#105;&#111;&#110;&#046;&#099;&#111;&#046;&#117;&#107;\">&#105;&#110;&#102;&#111;&#064;&#103;&#108;&#111;&#098;&#097;&#108;&#109;&#101;&#100;&#105;&#097;&#116;&#105;&#111;&#110;&#046;&#099;&#111;&#046;&#117;&#107;</a><br />\n<strong>Telephone:</strong> 0800 064 4488<br />\n<strong>Fax:</strong> 0208 441 4101</p>\n</div>\n\n<h3>South West England</h3>\n\n<div class=\"contact\">\n<p><a href=\"http://www.wessexmediation.co.uk/\" title=\"Wessex Mediation Service\" rel=\"external\">Wessex Mediation Service</a><br />\n<strong>Email:</strong> <a href=\"&#109;&#097;&#105;&#108;&#116;&#111;:&#105;&#110;&#102;&#111;&#064;&#119;&#101;&#115;&#115;&#101;&#120;&#109;&#101;&#100;&#105;&#097;&#116;&#105;&#111;&#110;&#046;&#099;&#111;&#046;&#117;&#107;\">&#105;&#110;&#102;&#111;&#064;&#119;&#101;&#115;&#115;&#101;&#120;&#109;&#101;&#100;&#105;&#097;&#116;&#105;&#111;&#110;&#046;&#099;&#111;&#046;&#117;&#107;</a><br />\n<strong>Telephone:</strong> 08450 529 487<br />\n<strong>Fax:</strong> 01823 352 210</p>\n</div>\n\n<h3>West Midlands</h3>\n\n<div class=\"contact\">\n<p><a href=\"http://www.mediation-works.co.uk/\" title=\"Mediation Works\" rel=\"external\">Mediation Works</a><br />\n<strong>Email:</strong> <a href=\"&#109;&#097;&#105;&#108;&#116;&#111;:&#111;&#102;&#102;&#105;&#099;&#101;&#064;&#109;&#105;&#100;&#108;&#097;&#110;&#100;&#115;&#115;&#101;&#110;&#109;&#101;&#100;&#105;&#097;&#116;&#105;&#111;&#110;&#046;&#099;&#111;&#109;\">&#111;&#102;&#102;&#105;&#099;&#101;&#064;&#109;&#105;&#100;&#108;&#097;&#110;&#100;&#115;&#115;&#101;&#110;&#109;&#101;&#100;&#105;&#097;&#116;&#105;&#111;&#110;&#046;&#099;&#111;&#109;</a><br />\n<strong>Telephone:</strong> 01952 275 038<br />\n<strong>Fax:</strong> 01952 224 281</p>\n</div>\n"}},{"part":{"web_url":"https://www.gov.uk/special-educational-needs-disability-tribunal/appeal-to-tribunal","slug":"appeal-to-tribunal","order":3,"title":"Appeal to the tribunal","body":"<p>To appeal, fill in the form below, giving reasons why you disagree with the council&rsquo;s decision.</p>\n\n<div class=\"form-download\">\n<p><a href=\"http://www.justice.gov.uk/downloads/forms/tribunals/send/sen-appeal-form.pdf\" title=\"Download 'Appeal form' (PDF, 44KB)\" rel=\"external\">Download \u2018Appeal form\u2019 (PDF, 44KB)</a></p>\n</div>\n\n<p>Send this, with the documents listed on the form, to:</p>\n\n<div class=\"address\"><div class=\"adr org fn\"><p>\n First-tier Tribunal (Special Educational Needs and Disability)  \nMowden Hall  \n<br />Staindrop Road  \n<br />Darlington  \n<br />DL3 9BG \n</p></div></div>\n\n<div class=\"contact\">\n<p><strong>Email:</strong> <a href=\"&#109;&#097;&#105;&#108;&#116;&#111;:&#115;&#101;&#110;&#100;&#105;&#115;&#116;&#113;&#117;&#101;&#114;&#105;&#101;&#115;&#064;&#104;&#109;&#099;&#116;&#115;&#046;&#103;&#115;&#105;&#046;&#103;&#111;&#118;&#046;&#117;&#107;\">&#115;&#101;&#110;&#100;&#105;&#115;&#116;&#113;&#117;&#101;&#114;&#105;&#101;&#115;&#064;&#104;&#109;&#099;&#116;&#115;&#046;&#103;&#115;&#105;&#046;&#103;&#111;&#118;&#046;&#117;&#107;</a><br />\n<strong>Telephone:</strong> 01325 392 760<br />\n<strong>Fax:</strong> 01325 391 080<br />\nor 01325 391 310</p>\n</div>\n\n<p>It usually takes 5 months to get a decision on a case from the date of the appeal.</p>\n"}},{"part":{"web_url":"https://www.gov.uk/special-educational-needs-disability-tribunal/going-to-tribunal-hearing","slug":"going-to-tribunal-hearing","order":4,"title":"Going to a tribunal hearing","body":"<p>The tribunal will hold the hearing at a regional hearing centre.</p>\n\n<p>You don&rsquo;t have to go to the hearing, but you may want to ask the council questions and put your case in person.</p>\n\n<p>Fill in the attendance form if you want to bring:</p>\n\n<ul>\n  <li>someone to represent you</li>\n  <li>someone to support you at the hearing</li>\n</ul>\n\n<div class=\"form-download\">\n<p><a href=\"http://www.justice.gov.uk/downloads/forms/tribunals/send/parents-attend-form.pdf\" title=\"Download 'attendance form' (PDF, 61KB)\" rel=\"external\">Download \u2018attendance form\u2019 (PDF, 61KB)</a></p>\n</div>\n\n<h2>Who will be at the hearing</h2>\n\n<p>The hearing will usually be attended by:</p>\n\n<ul>\n  <li>up to 3 tribunal members</li>\n  <li>a tribunal clerk</li>\n  <li>someone representing the council</li>\n  <li>any witnesses</li>\n</ul>\n\n<p>Both parents can attend.</p>\n\n<p>You are usually allowed to bring up to 3 witnesses to a hearing. </p>\n\n<p>You may not have to call professional witnesses if they have already written a report on your child.</p>\n\n<p>You can bring your child, but you&rsquo;ll have to arrange for someone to look after them when they&rsquo;re not in the hearing room.</p>\n\n<h2>Travel costs</h2>\n\n<p>You and your witnesses will be able to claim for travel expenses for going to the hearing.</p>\n\n<p>If you bring a friend or relative to the hearing, you will also be able to claim for their travel costs.</p>\n\n<p>The tribunal clerk will give you the forms you need.</p>\n\n<div class=\"application-notice info-notice\">\n<p>You will usually get the tribunal\u2019s decision in the post within 10 days of the hearing.</p>\n</div>\n"}},{"part":{"web_url":"https://www.gov.uk/special-educational-needs-disability-tribunal/if-you-win-your-appeal","slug":"if-you-win-your-appeal","order":5,"title":"If you win your appeal","body":"<p>If you win your appeal, the council must act on the tribunal&rsquo;s decision within a fixed amount of time:</p>\n\n<table>\n  <thead>\n    <tr>\n      <th>Decision</th>\n      <th>When council must act on decision</th>\n    </tr>\n  </thead>\n  <tbody>\n    <tr>\n      <td>Start assessment or reassessment</td>\n      <td>within 4 weeks</td>\n    </tr>\n    <tr>\n      <td>Make statement of child&rsquo;s needs</td>\n      <td>within 5 weeks</td>\n    </tr>\n    <tr>\n      <td>Change statement</td>\n      <td>within 5 weeks</td>\n    </tr>\n    <tr>\n      <td>Change the school</td>\n      <td>within 2 weeks</td>\n    </tr>\n    <tr>\n      <td>Continue with statement of child&rsquo;s needs</td>\n      <td>at once</td>\n    </tr>\n    <tr>\n      <td>Cancel a statement</td>\n      <td>at once</td>\n    </tr>\n  </tbody>\n</table>\n\n<p>If the council doesn&rsquo;t keep to the decision you can complain to the Local Government Ombudsman:</p>\n\n<div class=\"contact\">\n<p><strong>Local Government Ombudsman</strong><br />\n<a href=\"http://www.lgo.org.uk/forms/ShowForm.asp?fm_fid=74\" title=\"enquiry form\" rel=\"external\">Enquiry form</a><br />\n<strong>Telephone:</strong> 0300 061 0614</p>\n</div>\n\n<div class=\"address\"><div class=\"adr org fn\"><p>\n Local Government Ombudsman    \n\n<br />PO Box 4771  \n<br />Coventry  \n<br />CV4 0EH \n</p></div></div>\n"}},{"part":{"web_url":"https://www.gov.uk/special-educational-needs-disability-tribunal/if-you-lose-your-appeal","slug":"if-you-lose-your-appeal","order":6,"title":"If you lose your appeal","body":"<p>If you lose your case, you may be able to:</p>\n\n<ul>\n  <li>ask the tribunal to look at the case again, or overturn it</li>\n  <li>appeal against the decision</li>\n</ul>\n\n<p>The tribunal will send you details of how you can ask for the decision to be reviewed or &lsquo;set aside&rsquo;.</p>\n\n<p>To appeal against the decision, fill in the <a rel=\"external\" href=\"http://hmctsformfinder.justice.gov.uk/HMCTS/GetForm.do?court_forms_id=2767\" title=\"application for permission to appeal form\">application for permission to appeal form.</a></p>\n\n<p>Send this to the special educational needs tribunal:</p>\n\n<div class=\"address\"><div class=\"adr org fn\"><p>\n First-tier Tribunal (Special Educational Needs and Disability)  \nMowden Hall  \n<br />Staindrop Road  \n<br />Darlington  \n<br />DL3 9BG \n</p></div></div>\n\n<div class=\"contact\">\n<p><strong>Email:</strong> <a href=\"&#109;&#097;&#105;&#108;&#116;&#111;:&#115;&#101;&#110;&#100;&#105;&#115;&#116;&#113;&#117;&#101;&#114;&#105;&#101;&#115;&#064;&#104;&#109;&#099;&#116;&#115;&#046;&#103;&#115;&#105;&#046;&#103;&#111;&#118;&#046;&#117;&#107;\">&#115;&#101;&#110;&#100;&#105;&#115;&#116;&#113;&#117;&#101;&#114;&#105;&#101;&#115;&#064;&#104;&#109;&#099;&#116;&#115;&#046;&#103;&#115;&#105;&#046;&#103;&#111;&#118;&#046;&#117;&#107;</a><br />\n<strong>Telephone:</strong> 01325 392 760<br />\n<strong>Fax:</strong> 01325 391 080<br />\nor 01325 391 310</p>\n</div>\n\n<div class=\"application-notice help-notice\">\n<p>You must appeal within 28 days of the date of the tribunal\u2019s decision letter.</p>\n</div>\n\n<p>If you&rsquo;re given permission to appeal, the case will be heard by a higher tribunal called the <a rel=\"external\" href=\"http://www.justice.gov.uk/tribunals/aa\" title=\"Upper Tribunal (Administrative Appeals Chamber)\">Upper Tribunal (Administrative Appeals Chamber).</a></p>\n"}}]}